laboratory_examinations.findings: Bilateral small pleural effusions, right greater than left, with associated compressive atelectasis. The pancreas is enlarged and edematous, with surrounding fat stranding and trace free fluid. No obstructing stone or mass is identified. A 1.8 cm simple cyst in the interpolar region of the right kidney is noted.
